    "description": "A finite-element model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of peak von Mises stress and fatigue safety factor to variations in stem geometry and cortical bone modulus for a cementless total hip stem used in primary total hip arthroplasty. Model influence is MEDIUM (bench-top mechanical testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact implant fatigue life and patient safety). Model Risk Level 3.",
