      "rationale": "Systematic mesh refinement study conducted across three mesh densities using Richardson extrapolation per Roache (1998). GCI for peak von Mises stress at the critical neck cross-section: 1.8% (fine mesh selected for production runs). Apparent order of convergence p = 1.97, consistent with quadratic elements. Local mesh refinement applied at stress concentrations (fillet radii, screw hole interfaces) confirmed via element quality metrics (Jacobian ratio > 0.7 throughout). Validation result VR003 directly supports this factor."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-ortho-ac-tc",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions replicated ISO 7206-4:2010 loading protocol with documented load cell calibration (NIST-traceable, ±0.5% accuracy), fixture alignment verification (±0.5°), and environmental controls (23 ± 2°C, humidity 50 ± 5%). Test matrix covers 7 load configurations spanning the clinical envelope of single-leg stance to stair-climbing. Boundary condition fidelity assessed by comparing fixture reaction forces against FE model predictions; agreement within 3%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-ortho-ac-oc",
      "rationale": "Quantitative output comparison performed using mean absolute percent error (MAPE), 95% prediction intervals, and Bland-Altman analysis for all 12 strain-gauge locations. MAPE = 4.2%; all predictions within ±8% of measured values; no systematic bias detected (Bland-Altman mean difference −0.3 με, 95% limits of agreement ±18 με). Full-field DIC comparison for cadaveric specimens yields r = 0.96. Fatigue life predictions within factor-of-1.3 of experimental median. Exceeds required Gradation 3 threshold; Gradation 4 achieved through multi-metric quantitative comparison with statistical uncertainty bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-ortho-ac-rqi",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is peak von Mises stress at the stem neck and fatigue safety factor (SF = σ_endurance / σ_peak). These quantities directly govern the regulatory acceptance criterion (SF ≥ 1.5) and are the quantities measured in the ISO 7206-4 experimental protocol. Secondary QoIs (proximal load transfer index, interface micromotion) are also tracked and validated. Traceability matrix linking QoIs to regulatory requirements (21 CFR 888.3310) documented in requirements traceability report RTM-2025-001."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-ortho-ac-rva",
      "rationale": "Validation activities directly address the COU: (1) ISO 7206-4 bench testing replicates clinical loading conditions; (2) cadaveric specimens span the target patient bone density range (BMD 0.6–1.1 g/cm²); (3) material coupon fatigue data obtained from the same Ti-6Al-4V alloy and surface finish as the production implant. Validation hierarchy documented per ASME V&V 40 §6.3: component-level coupon → sub-system bench → system cadaveric. Gaps between validation conditions and COU identified and bounded by sensitivity analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-ortho-ac-nse",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver convergence monitored via force and displacement residual norms; convergence criterion set at 1×10⁻⁶ (relative). Nonlinear contact iterations confirmed converged for all 7 load configurations (Newton-Raphson, < 12 iterations per load step). Solver round-off error assessed via double-precision arithmetic verification; negligible contribution to total numerical error budget (< 0.01% of GCI). Meets MRL 3 requirement at Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-ortho-ac-ue",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, material assignments, and load application performed by a second qualified FE analyst not involved in original model construction. Review checklist aligned with FDA guidance on computational modeling submissions. All discrepancies resolved prior to production runs. Simulation input files archived with checksums; re-run reproducibility confirmed (peak stress reproducible to < 0.1% across three independent re-runs on the same hardware)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-ortho-ac-mf",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic constitutive model selected for Ti-6Al-4V stem (yield stress 880 MPa; peak predicted stress 320 MPa — well within elastic regime). Cortical bone modeled as transversely isotropic elastic (E_axial = 18 GPa, E_transverse = 12 GPa) based on published nanoindentation data. Contact mechanics at stem-bone interface modeled with Coulomb friction (μ = 0.3, literature-supported). Model form assumptions documented and sensitivity analysis performed: ±20% variation in bone modulus yields ±11% variation in peak stem stress, consistent with published parametric studies. Model form uncertainty quantified and incorporated into overall uncertainty budget."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-ortho-ac-mi",
      "rationale": "All model inputs traceable to primary sources: (1) implant geometry from certified CMM measurement report (tolerance ±0.02 mm); (2) material properties from ASTM F136 certificate of conformance and supplementary coupon test data; (3) loading conditions from ISO 7206-4 and published gait analysis literature (Bergmann et al. 2001, DOI 10.1016/S0021-9290(01)00040-9); (4) bone geometry from CT scan segmentation with documented threshold and smoothing protocol. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo sampling (1000 samples); 95th-percentile peak stress used as conservative design value."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-ortho-ac-ts",
      "rationale": "Validation test samples include: (1) 6 surrogate composite femur specimens (Sawbones 4th generation, ISO 7206-4 compliant) for strain-gauge validation; (2) 4 fresh-frozen cadaveric femora (donor age 55–72, BMD confirmed by DXA) for full-field DIC validation; (3) 30 Ti-6Al-4V material coupons (ASTM E466 geometry) for fatigue characterization. Sample sizes justified by power analysis (β = 0.80, α = 0.05). Specimen traceability documented with unique identifiers; storage and preparation protocols recorded per ASTM F2504."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
